## 6

Akkodis is seeking an Apple Mac System Administrator for a contract position with a client in Scarborough, ON. The ideal candidate will have strong experience in macOS administration, as well as hands-on expertise with JAMF Pro and JAMF 300 or 400 certification.
Position: Apple MAC System Admin
Location: Scarborough, ON
Long-Term Contract

Job Description
Key Responsibilities:
Write and deploy custom Bash scripts to uninstall unauthorized or unnecessary applications across the Mac fleet
Administer and maintain the JAMF Pro environment across 1500 macOS devices
Maintain system integrity by enforcing compliance standards and improving endpoint security posture
Collaborate with Security, Infrastructure, and Application teams to ensure Mac devices align with corporate standards
Provide advanced troubleshooting and support for JAMF-related issues
Assist with system audits, reporting, and automation of operational tasks
Stay current with macOS, JAMF, and scripting best practices and implement improvements accordingly

Requirement:
5+ years of experience in macOS administration, with at least 3 years dedicated to JAMF Pro
Expert-level proficiency in Bash scripting, especially for application removal and system configuration on macOS
Proven experience automating large-scale app uninstalls and device configuration using JAMF
Familiarity with extension attributes, smart groups, policies, and JAMF API
Strong understanding of macOS security principles, including device hardening and compliance enforcement
Comfortable working in enterprise environments with thousands of endpoints
Excellent communication skills and the ability to document processes clearly
Experience with version control systems (e.g., Git) is an asset
JAMF 300 or 400 certification is preferred

Nice to Have:
Experience with Python or Swift for macOS automation
Familiarity with Apple Business Manager
Exposure to MDM migrations or zero-touch deployment strategies

